00:41:52,316 --> 00:41:56,619
are handed powerful tools but never taught how to think deeply about their work and about

735
00:41:56,659 --> 00:41:57,279
themselves?

736
00:41:58,040 --> 00:41:59,981
I believe they do have the life experience.

737
00:42:00,341 --> 00:42:02,922
Undergrads are young, but they have still seen a lot.

738
00:42:02,963 --> 00:42:03,843
They've done a lot.

739
00:42:04,223 --> 00:42:06,464
But they need our help to understand it

740
00:42:06,564 --> 00:42:09,326
and to parse all of that information that swirls

741
00:42:09,406 --> 00:42:11,167
around their weird little souls.

742
00:42:13,040 --> 00:42:14,381
So we're still trying to figure it out.

743
00:42:14,501 --> 00:42:16,063
And I don't know that I have the answers.

744
00:42:16,323 --> 00:42:18,765
I have ideas about what the answers might look like,

745
00:42:19,146 --> 00:42:20,687
but I can't do it alone either.

746
00:42:21,268 --> 00:42:22,609
We need collaboration,

747
00:42:22,829 --> 00:42:25,011
especially between industry and academia,

748
00:42:25,412 --> 00:42:27,474
and lots more crossover between them.

749
00:42:27,994 --> 00:42:29,876
Getting more professionals involved in education

750
00:42:29,936 --> 00:42:32,238
is not just for the students, it is also for the faculty.

751
00:42:32,659 --> 00:42:33,740
Triple A independent.

752
00:42:34,540 --> 00:42:38,141
game designer, developer, artist, journalist, producer, whatever your role is, it doesn't

753
00:42:38,221 --> 00:42:43,022
matter. The variety pack is ideal. So what can you do? Well, there's adjunct teaching.

754
00:42:43,462 --> 00:42:47,223
You can teach little courses over a semester and you get a few grand and you get to meet

755
