My talented friend Lisa Brown did that at Harrisburg University for a whole year.

764
00:43:15,713 --> 00:43:17,314
And does she want to be a teacher her whole life?

765
00:43:17,354 --> 00:43:17,414
No.

766
00:43:17,434 --> 00:43:18,514
She's a teacher.

767
00:43:18,534 --> 00:43:18,874
She's a teacher.

768
00:43:18,894 --> 00:43:19,214
She's a teacher.

769
00:43:19,234 --> 00:43:19,674
She's a teacher.

770
00:43:19,694 --> 00:43:20,034
She's a teacher.

771
00:43:20,055 --> 00:43:20,515
She's a teacher.

772
00:43:20,695 --> 00:43:22,376
but it was great and the students are better for it.

773
00:43:22,717 --> 00:43:24,779
You get benefits, funding, all that good stuff.

774
00:43:25,019 --> 00:43:26,300
Collaboration with faculty.

775
00:43:26,640 --> 00:43:28,242
Video call sessions with classes.

776
00:43:28,502 --> 00:43:31,224
Right now we are working on a game capstone,

777
00:43:31,264 --> 00:43:32,426
which is really, really hard to do.

778
00:43:32,966 --> 00:43:34,768
Trying to emulate the trials and tribulations

779
00:43:34,808 --> 00:43:36,549
of small teams or studios working to create

780
00:43:36,569 --> 00:43:38,611
professionally viable game experiences.

781
00:43:39,332 --> 00:43:40,613
And Young Horses is doing that.

782
00:43:40,853 --> 00:43:45,156
It's taking only a few hours of their time, but they're allowing us a way to examine what

783
00:43:45,196 --> 00:43:45,857
it is they want.

784
00:43:45,897 --> 00:43:46,838
What are their values?

785
00:43:46,938 --> 00:43:48,479
What it is that they care about?

786
00:43:48,879 --> 00:43:54,363
And how do we create something or pitch something that actually makes that happen?

787
00:43:56,105 --> 00:44:04,247
Teaching may sound super duper scary, you may feel unqualified, ineloquent, and a bunch of strange people staring at you, imposter syndrome, all that good stuff.

788
00:44:04,267 --> 00:44:10,168
So here's some tips. You know who else is scared? Undergrads. They're super scared. Way more scared of you than you are of them.

789
00:44:10,848 --> 00:44:18,710
You only need to be a step ahead of them in most things. The real stuff is your experience, your wisdom, your lessons learned through blood, sweat, tears, and time.

